<h2 id="section-top">Diabetic Medicine</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1155">Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContente6f85c8f67874af8b9938ef33ed6b85a">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Testing blood sugar levels" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=24913"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>The Diabetes Service provides a highly specialist level of education, assessment, treatment and management for children and adults with type 1 diabetes, type 2 diabetes and impaired glucose tolerance who are registered with a Salford General Practitioner and a number of out of area patients.Â  Find out more by <a href="http://www.srft.nhs.uk/about-us/depts/diabetes-service/">visiting our section on the Salford Royal website</a>.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>All facets of the service are focused on developing and supporting patients with the principles of self-management.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
